title: Kyrgyzstan's central bank cuts policy rate by 25 bp
text:
May 29, 2018 / 4:14 AM / Updated an hour ago Kyrgyzstan's central bank cuts policy rate by 25 bp
BISHKEK, May 29 (Reuters) - Kyrgyzstanâ€™s central bank cut its policy rate to 4.75 percent from 5.00 percent on Tuesday, it said in a statement, citing moderate inflation and positive economic growth dynamics. (Reporting by Olga Dzyubenko Writing by Olzhas Auyezov; Editing by Gopakumar Warrier)
